title: Investigation of activation cross-sections of deuteron induced reactions on vanadium up to 40 MeV

x4freetext: Investigation of activation cross-sections of deuteron
induced reactions on vanadium up to 40 MeV

x4codes.hlp: Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.269, p.1792 (2011)

x4freetext: High purity (99.98%) natural V from Goodfellow
MeV were used. Target and monitor foils were
irradiated in Faraday-cup type holder. Measurements
started after 1h cooling time for 21 MeV irradiation
and 1 day cooling time of 40 MeV irradiation.
The beam intensities obtained via  charge
collection were corrected with the data from the
monitor reaction. The energy degradation was
initially determined by calculation using  the
formulas and tables of Andersen and Ziegler and
corrected on the basis of the measured monitor
reaction excitation function. The nuclear data
were taken from the NUDAT2 database.
incident energy is estimated to be 0.3 MeV while due
to cumulative effects the uncertainty increases to
1.3 MeV on the last foils of the stack.
